title: Outback Queensland Pub Featured In ‘Crocodile Dundee’ Finds New Owners | 10 News+
description: The Walkabout Creek Hotel, in the outback Queensland town of McKinlay, has found new ownership after three years on the market. The pub was made famous when it was featured in the classic film ‘Crocodile Dundee’ nearly four decades ago. 10 News+ was joined by local cattle grazier Angus Brodie, who now owns the pub with his wife Jo Cranney. title: At Least 36 Dead, Hundreds Missing, After Hong Kong High-Rise Fire | 10 News
description: Hong Kong leader John Lee has confirmed 36 people, including a firefighter, have been killed after a fire engulfed a high-rise apartment complex in Hong Kong on Wednesday.  Initial investigations show the walls were unusually flammable. Authorities say the towers had been sheathed in bamboo scaffolding, and styrofoam had been used to seal windows.  At least 279 people are missing, while around 900 people have been evacuated to shelters.  Lee extended his “deepest condolences” to those affected, marking the fire as the city's deadliest in three decades.  #10News #HongKong  Join the conversation and follow us on: TikTok: http://www.tiktok.com/@10NewsAU/ Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/10NewsAU/ Twitter: http://twitter.com/10NewsAU Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/10NewsAU/  10 News airs at 5pm, seven nights a week in your local market on Network 10. title: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese Says 'Hearts Of Australians With Hong Kong' | 10 News
description: Australian Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has expressed sympathy for the people of Hong Kong after a fire engulfed a high-rise apartment complex in the region on Wednesday.  “This has been a human tragedy, and the hearts of all Australians today will be thinking of the people of Hong Kong who are going through a very tough day,” Albanese said.  Hong Kong’s leader John Lee confirmed 36 people, including a firefighter, have been killed and 279 more are missing. title: Two National Guard Soldiers Critically Injured In Targeted Washington, D.C. Shooting | 10 News
description: Two National Guard soldiers were critically wounded in a targeted ambush near the White House after a gunman walked up and opened fire on their afternoon patrol.  Police say the lone suspect was shot and taken into custody within moments as emergency crews rushed to stabilise the troops at the scene.  The Trump administration has ordered an additional 500 Guard members into Washington, D.C., with officials, including FBI director Kash Patel, condemning the “brazen” attack.  Confusion briefly spread after West Virginia’s governor wrongly announced both soldiers had died, before backtracking and saying their conditions remained uncertain. title: Cambridge University Study Reveals Why You May Be Younger Than You Think | 10 News
description: New research has revealed you might be younger than you think, or at least your brain is.  A Cambridge University study scanned the brains of almost 4,000 people up to the age of 90, revealing the brain goes through five distinct phases, with turning points coming at the ages of 9, 32, 66 and 83.  10’s Late News explains.
